Bungoma police are investigating a suspected arson fire that damaged a dormitory in Chesamis Boyâ€™s High School, Kimilili, on Saturday. The building had 170 students. More than 10 students were slightly injured in a stampede as they ran for safety at 8pm. Police said they found a container they suspect contained petrol used to burn the dorm. Principal Ezekiel Ayiego said the fire might have been started by unruly students. He said prefects and teachers are helping with the investigation. Students tried to put out the fire with water, sand and twigs but it overwhelmed them. Injured students were treated and discharged from Kimilili Hospital. They returned to school. All property was destroyed.Students share beds with classmates in other dorms.